Honest review of @animeink_con Miami 

The convention center was beautiful, lighting was way better than any other I’ve worked. The people I met were welcoming and nice and excited to be there. 

I was able to do one tattoo, on a very nice guy who wanted something my style. 

The attendance was extremely low, which I think was a collective bummer for most artists (who weren’t booked up at all, maybe don’t have clients in Miami. Me included) That being said, its no one’s responsibility or problem to Make sure each artist has work to do and is happy. So if we weren’t busy, we chose to take the risk and hopefully get walk-ups. Sometimes it just doesn’t pan out. 

That being said, the promotion was lacking. Strictly internet and IG promo just doesn’t seem to cut it for a more niche event like this, but I’m not a marketing expert. So who knows, I could be completely wrong. 

The Family feeling wasn’t present like my previous experience in Richmond. 

I prob won’t be attending this particular event again, but I still had fun exploring Miami and meeting everyone I got the chance to! 

Thanks @cutiemarietattoos and @lolasounds for being amazing friends, wife’s and travel buds 💖💖💖

Thanks for you time, and reading a review no one asked for 🤠
 
-Dyl

Tattoo Machines I use!
 
I have recently made the transition back into using hybrid/coil machines for line work. 

While pens and a cartridges work well for most people. I found my self struggling to get truly rich bold line work. I was always fighting with the system to get the results I wanted. 

On the other hand, for black and grey shading, I love using a pen. The versatility to be cordless really comes in handy , esp with larger work like Back Pieces.

Hybrids and coils are louder , and seem more aggressive at first sight. I have noticed that they hurt less, don’t cause scar tissue nearly as easily and get the job done in one pass.

I’m sorry to my coworkers who like it quiet , but nothing beats lining with these . 

Machines 
- @criticaltattoosupply  Torque 4.2mm
- @dankubin Sidewinder v7b
- @andy_seb_machines IWO rca version
